13
nondomiciled commercial driver's licenses may be subject to
revocation under subsection (f).
(i) A nondomiciled commercial driver's license issued prior to
March 1, 2026, to an individual who:
(1) is domiciled in a foreign country; and
(2) does not hold H-2A, H-2B, or E-2 nonimmigrant status
under the Immigration and Nationality Act;
expires on April 1, 2026.
